1
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:41,200
(Touch Your Heart)

2
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:46,920
I had so much fun today.

3
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,920
That was a movie I've always
wanted to watch with you,

4
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,333
and I'm glad we got to
watch it like this.

5
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,233
Then thank goodness.

6
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,953
It was just so perfect!

7
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:02,686
My farewell party,
prepared by you.

8
00:01:02,766 --> 00:01:06,253
Actually, calling it a farewell
party sounds a little weird.

9
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:08,386
It's like we're breaking up.

10
00:01:08,466 --> 00:01:09,886
But it's just that we won't be
seeing each other at the

11
00:01:09,966 --> 00:01:11,620
law firm anymore, right?

12
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:13,900
Though that makes me sad, too...

13
00:01:20,466 --> 00:01:21,966
Ms. Oh Yoon-seo.

14
00:01:24,366 --> 00:01:28,300
Why are you calling me Yoon-seo?

15
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:30,600
Thanks to you,

16
00:01:32,666 --> 00:01:34,066
I was very happy.

17
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:39,433
Why are you saying this?

18
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,066
Just like that movie,

19
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:49,566
I want you to return to
your place as Oh Yoon-seo,

20
00:01:51,966 --> 00:01:56,866
and me, to where I ought to be.

21
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,400
What do you mean, Mr. Kwon?

22
00:02:19,366 --> 00:02:20,433
Let's...

23
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:26,100
...break up.

24
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:35,286
Why are you saying that
all of a sudden?

25
00:02:35,366 --> 00:02:37,433
Did I do something wrong?

26
00:02:41,233 --> 00:02:43,153
Is it because I deceived you?

27
00:02:43,233 --> 00:02:45,253
Did you feel betrayed,
now that you thought about it?

28
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,533
Or…

29
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:52,533
Did it bother you that our picture
was uploaded on the Internet?

30
00:02:53,166 --> 00:02:55,086
You felt burdened by

31
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:56,633
all this unwanted attention?

32
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,666
Say something, please.

33
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:04,166
Why should we break up?

34
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:08,966
Yes.

35
00:03:10,866 --> 00:03:12,966
It's because of all the
reasons you mentioned,

36
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:17,253
that I decided it was too much for
me to continue our relationship.

37
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,433
So…

38
00:03:19,966 --> 00:03:22,933
I think it's best
we leave it here.

39
00:03:23,633 --> 00:03:24,900
Mr. Kwon…

40
00:03:29,066 --> 00:03:30,100
Thank you,

41
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:33,966
for everything up until now.

42
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,800
(Episode 13)

43
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:04,433
Yoon-seo!

44
00:05:06,233 --> 00:05:07,400
Oh Yoon-seo!

45
00:05:08,766 --> 00:05:10,133
Is she still in bed?

46
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,833
Yoon-seo!

47
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:15,966
Yoon-seo.

48
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,866
What's wrong?

49
00:05:20,066 --> 00:05:22,133
Yoon-seo, have you been crying?

50
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:27,153
- Hyuk-jun…
- Sure, sure.

51
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:29,153
I'm here for you. I'm right here,

52
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,720
so tell me everything.

53
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,053
What's the matter, Yoon-seo?

54
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:35,533
Mr. Kwon wants to break up.

55
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,953
What?

56
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:42,466
He says it's best
we leave it here.

57
00:05:47,266 --> 00:05:49,733
And he said he likes me…

58
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:56,333
And promised he'll always
be on my side…

59
00:06:00,266 --> 00:06:02,633
So how could he change like this,
all of a sudden?

60
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:08,686
How could he just end this
with those few words?

61
00:06:08,766 --> 00:06:11,986
This is my first time
breaking up with anyone,

62
00:06:12,066 --> 00:06:15,333
so I just don't know what to do.

63
00:06:24,366 --> 00:06:26,253
Uh… Yoon-seo, first of all,

64
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:28,820
you're supposed to pick up
your stuff from the office today,

65
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:31,666
but I'll do that for you instead.
You just rest.

66
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:33,920
No, no. I'll go.

67
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,086
No, Yoon-seo.

68
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:37,386
I don't think you're in the
right state to do that.

69
00:06:37,466 --> 00:06:40,000
Still… I need to see Mr. Kwon.

70
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,833
But… Yoon-seo.

71
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,333
Yoon-seo!

72
00:06:53,766 --> 00:06:54,686
Mr. Yeon,

73
00:06:54,766 --> 00:06:56,366
why are you sighing like that?

74
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,853
It somehow feels
so dark in the office.

75
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,653
Did a bulb get blown?

76
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:05,386
No, Mr. Yeon. I don't think so.

77
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:08,620
All six lights are
working as they should,

78
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:11,020
each in their own place.

79
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,186
Really?

80
00:07:12,266 --> 00:07:14,666
But why does it feel so
dark and gloomy in here?

81
00:07:16,366 --> 00:07:18,000
Is it because Yoon-seo is
no longer here?

82
00:07:18,966 --> 00:07:20,033
That's it.

83
00:07:20,366 --> 00:07:21,920
With our sparkling goddess gone,

84
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,820
there's just no more life
in the office.

85
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:26,786
I have to agree. Somehow it…

86
00:07:26,866 --> 00:07:27,786
It feels quite empty.

87
00:07:27,866 --> 00:07:29,186
Even we're feeling it,

88
00:07:29,266 --> 00:07:31,620
so imagine how it must be
for Mr. Kwon.

89
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,953
Yoon-seo's been exceptional
as his secretary,

90
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:37,520
so he must feel her absence a lot.

91
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,700
Much like…

92
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,953
…a young deer who is dejected that

93
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:43,733
he now has no place to return.

94
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:46,686
Well, I don't know about
this "young deer,"

95
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:49,653
but Ms. Yang, please do your best
to support Kwon.

96
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:51,800
- Sure, I'll do that.
- Thanks.

97
00:07:53,433 --> 00:07:54,753
Huh? Yoon-seo!

98
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,266
Hey, Yoon-seo!

99
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,920
What brings you here?

100
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,800
I thought you weren't
coming in, starting today.

101
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,720
Well…

102
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,086
I'm here to pick up my belongings.

103
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:07,286
Oh, we could've
posted them to you.

104
00:08:07,366 --> 00:08:09,820
No need to come all this way!

105
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,000
Just because…

106
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:25,433
Somehow, Yoon-seo looks
a little down today.

107
00:09:37,866 --> 00:09:39,166
Mr. Kwon.

108
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:43,533
I, uh…

109
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:46,400
I'll get going, then.

110
00:09:53,066 --> 00:09:54,566
I said, I'm leaving.

111
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:02,800
If you let me go like this,
then it's really over.

112
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,866
You're still not going to
look at me?

113
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,800
Thank you,

114
00:10:39,666 --> 00:10:41,333
for everything up until now.

115
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:47,766
I wish you all the best for
your future.

116
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,366
(It's alright, anytime)

117
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:43,653
Hey.

118
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:46,620
If you're free tonight,
want to have a drink?

119
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:48,533
Sure, let's do that.

120
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:52,200
I was just in the mood, too.

121
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:56,666
Kwon Jung-rok.

122
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,866
Oh what? Why are you two together?

123
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,400
We decided to get back together.

124
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:18,286
Yeo-reum was just too clingy,

125
00:13:18,366 --> 00:13:20,066
so I decided to take her back.

126
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,220
I really gave up at her

127
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:25,120
tenacity to win love back.

128
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,220
Don't start making a joke
in front of Jung-rok again.

129
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:29,253
You know he takes
everything seriously.

130
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,020
Hey, no.

131
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,820
You just don't know it yet.

132
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:35,253
He's not that serious,

133
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:36,620
hard-minded Kwon Jung-rok
he was before.

134
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:38,333
He's sure changed a lot.

135
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:41,986
Being in a relationship has
softened him up.

136
00:13:42,066 --> 00:13:43,620
- Really?
- Of course.

137
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,700
I mean it!

138
00:13:46,566 --> 00:13:50,400
If he was all dried up like
this dry squid before,

139
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:53,320
love has changed him
into a big softie,

140
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,966
so squishy like this folded egg.

141
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,386
What's with your expression?

142
00:14:00,466 --> 00:14:02,486
You don't like my metaphor?

143
00:14:02,566 --> 00:14:04,900
Well, I think Yoon-seo will
agree with me.

144
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,853
Now that we're on the topic,

145
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,753
why don’t you ask
Yoon-seo to join us?

146
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:14,120
Yes, ask her if she wants to
join us, if she's free.

147
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,486
You better hold onto your heart.

148
00:14:15,566 --> 00:14:17,153
You'll be shocked to see

149
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:19,466
just how hard he's fallen for her.

150
00:14:21,266 --> 00:14:22,386
Come on!

151
00:14:22,466 --> 00:14:23,733
Call her already.

152
00:14:26,066 --> 00:14:27,520
Wait a second.

153
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:31,953
Is this place to humble for
someone like Yoon-seo?

154
00:14:32,033 --> 00:14:33,820
Should we go to
a fancy bar nearby?

155
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,686
Let's do that. It's too open here,

156
00:14:35,766 --> 00:14:37,120
and that might make
Yoon-seo feel uncomfortable.

157
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,253
- Right?
- Right.

158
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:39,633
No need.

159
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:44,020
Why? Are you worried that
we might bully her?

160
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,186
Look at this.

161
00:14:45,266 --> 00:14:47,500
This is how much
he cares for her, alright?

162
00:14:49,566 --> 00:14:50,866
We broke up.

163
00:14:52,366 --> 00:14:53,433
Just what…

164
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,886
What… But how?

165
00:15:00,966 --> 00:15:02,453
I guess me being here today will

166
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:05,020
only make it awkward for you guys,

167
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:08,553
so I'll catch up with you later.

168
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:10,300
I'm off first, so enjoy the
rest of your evening.

169
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:28,266
Kwon Jung-rok!

170
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,720
Hey.

171
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,186
You can't just go like this.

172
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:35,086
Let's have some soju.

173
00:15:35,166 --> 00:15:36,120
I told Yeo-reum to go ahead first.

174
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:39,000
- What for?
- What do you mean, what for?

175
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,420
I should've sensed
something was wrong

176
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,800
from your tone earlier…

177
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:48,133
Come on, hurry up!

178
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:56,686
Ma'am, can we get
another bottle here, please?

179
00:15:56,766 --> 00:15:57,833
Sure.

180
00:15:58,233 --> 00:16:00,420
So…

181
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,100
You let her go,
so she can be happy?

182
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:12,653
Why did you, when you knew
you'll have a hard time?

183
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:15,300
You should've just braced it all,
no matter what comes your way.

184
00:16:17,166 --> 00:16:20,353
I knew all too well

185
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:21,833
just how much she wanted this.

186
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:28,466
And they say
I might get in the way of

187
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:32,033
her way there.

188
00:16:34,766 --> 00:16:38,920
So there was nothing else
I could do to help.

189
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,166
Still…

190
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:46,220
Yoon-seo will now remember you
as that bastard who was

191
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:49,153
quick to have a change of heart,
without knowing anything.

192
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:50,333
And that's too…

193
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:57,566
So…

194
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:01,133
How did you bear it?

195
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:05,666
When you broke up with
Yeo-reum, I mean.

196
00:17:08,966 --> 00:17:10,766
How did you bear it?

197
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:23,653
However, in determining the
amount of loss incurred from

198
00:17:23,733 --> 00:17:27,020
copyright infringement, because
the software in question was

199
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,086
sold individually and separately,

200
00:17:29,166 --> 00:17:30,786
the scope of compensation
should also reflect

201
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:34,753
the actual damage done.

202
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,620
In regards to the said
overseas development project,

203
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,186
while investigating the slush funds,

204
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:40,053
we came to discover that
because of the differences in

205
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:42,153
valuation methods used
at home and abroad,

206
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:45,433
in reality he only incurred
$5 million worth of damages.

207
00:18:05,066 --> 00:18:09,820
As for the workers
who breached the law…

208
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:11,653
Your Honor, please
take into consideration,

209
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,320
that the software my client
developed during his time

210
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:17,086
at the company has generated
huge profit for the company.

211
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:19,086
We sincerely hope that
you will show as much

212
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:21,933
clemency as you can, for his case.

213
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,686
Alright, here's to Kwon,
who recorded top sales this month!

214
00:19:05,766 --> 00:19:07,500
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

215
00:19:10,966 --> 00:19:12,186
Kwon,

216
00:19:12,266 --> 00:19:14,053
you're like
a workaholic these days.

217
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:16,133
And I'm liking it!

218
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:22,753
I just wish you'd respond,
when I talk to you.

219
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:23,986
But…

220
00:19:24,066 --> 00:19:27,153
Is top in sales even
something to celebrate about?

221
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:28,386
Of course it's something!

222
00:19:28,466 --> 00:19:30,886
It's the momentum to propel
Always to a better tomorrow!

223
00:19:30,966 --> 00:19:32,286
Choi.

224
00:19:32,366 --> 00:19:34,666
When will we ever see you
become that momentum?

225
00:19:35,766 --> 00:19:37,286
You said you'll forget about
your sense of justice for

226
00:19:37,366 --> 00:19:39,653
the time being, for the
sake of sales,

227
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:41,820
but rather, you've been making me
wanting to forget you.

228
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,786
What? Don't say such a thing!

229
00:19:43,866 --> 00:19:46,320
That was just too harsh!

230
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:48,333
That should be my line.

231
00:19:49,066 --> 00:19:51,286
Did I offend you in any way?

232
00:19:51,366 --> 00:19:52,953
Is this your way of
protesting to me,

233
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,186
by terrorizing my eyes?

234
00:19:54,266 --> 00:19:55,786
You looked really threatening
when you did just now.

235
00:19:55,866 --> 00:19:59,920
Please, Mr. Yeon.
She looks just beautiful.

236
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,320
I couldn't have put it better.

237
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,753
You mind your own business.

238
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,633
For example,
you got sauce on your face.

239
00:20:07,233 --> 00:20:08,300
Do I?

240
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,153
This is really nothing,
but now that mention it

241
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:14,400
in front of anyone,
it's kind of embarrassing.

242
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:16,620
Wait a minute.

243
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:18,066
What's with this atmosphere?

244
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:20,920
Just now, Dan was defending Choi,

245
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,886
and now Choi's come to
Dan's defense.

246
00:20:22,966 --> 00:20:24,653
You can't fool me.

247
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:25,800
Don't tell me…

248
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,620
You've formed an alliance?

249
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,586
You've formed an alliance
as lawyers who don't sell,

250
00:20:31,666 --> 00:20:34,420
and are looking out for
each other, aren't you?

251
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,553
No way, Mr. Yeon.

252
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:37,653
Still, I like the way
things are now.

253
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:39,720
Before, they used to bicker
like the worst of enemies

254
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:43,353
but now they've warmed up
to each other,

255
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,153
like those cherry blossoms
lining the train tracks.

256
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,553
You're quite a poet,
aren't you, Mr. Lee.

257
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,686
Though you probably don't
know it yourself. Am I right?

258
00:20:49,766 --> 00:20:51,486
You might just become
a poet at this rate.

259
00:20:51,566 --> 00:20:52,486
Huh?

260
00:20:52,566 --> 00:20:56,053
Actually, that's my secret dream.

261
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:58,753
Really? Then why not write
a poem about me?

262
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,900
On the theme of charisma?

263
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:03,966
That's strong.

264
00:21:12,066 --> 00:21:13,586
By the way, why aren't you
smiling, Kwon?

265
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:15,153
You're so hard-faced,

266
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,500
and it's killing the mood.

267
00:21:17,466 --> 00:21:19,253
What if he doesn't smile?
At least he's competent.

268
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,586
As for you, Choi,
you can smile less and

269
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:22,653
bring me more results, alright?

270
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:24,020
Let's have a drink, Kwon.

271
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:25,153
With no smiles.

272
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:26,400
Oops, your glass is empty.

273
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:31,500
Alright, cheers, with no smiles!

274
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:37,600
Go on.

275
00:22:31,966 --> 00:22:33,966
(Oh Yoon-seo's Autograph Signing)

276
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:39,500
Yoon-seo!

277
00:22:49,266 --> 00:22:51,233
(Cosmic Goddess Oh Yoon-seo)

278
00:22:53,833 --> 00:22:54,753
(Writer: Lee Se-jin)

279
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:55,820
(Ju-ha, played by Oh Yoon-seo)

280
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:57,033
(Love is Bound to Hurt, Episode 2)

281
00:22:57,033 --> 00:22:59,420
You dropped this.

282
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,320
Why, thank you.

283
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:04,200
I really hate making
a faux pas like this one.

284
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,953
I hate people like that too,

285
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:09,220
and this is the first time that
I found it cute.

286
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:11,333
This is making me embarrassed.

287
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,700
But it's all fine when
it's for Yoon-seo, isn't it?

288
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,620
Hey.

289
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:21,533
Yoon-seo's at her rehearsal.

290
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,053
Ah!

291
00:23:23,133 --> 00:23:25,053
So she's doing well.

292
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:26,053
She looks beautiful in this photo.

293
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,120
Take a look.

294
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,586
Isn't Yoon-seo
beautiful, as always?

295
00:23:28,666 --> 00:23:30,153
Wow.

296
00:23:30,233 --> 00:23:31,420
For some reason,
she looks much happier than

297
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:33,386
when she was with us here.

298
00:23:33,466 --> 00:23:35,653
Is it because she's doing
what she really loves?

299
00:23:35,733 --> 00:23:38,300
Man… I really miss Yoon-seo.

300
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:40,086
Me too.

301
00:23:40,166 --> 00:23:43,420
Maybe she's grown on me,
but I've been missing her.

302
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:47,386
It was so much fun
chatting in the tea room…

303
00:23:47,466 --> 00:23:48,753
I miss her, too.

304
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:51,433
Right? It's not just me
who misses her, right?

305
00:23:53,866 --> 00:23:55,800
By the way, how come
you're not saying, Kwon?

306
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:58,500
Don't you miss Yoon-seo?

307
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,133
Can't you hear me?

308
00:24:03,266 --> 00:24:04,586
Anyways, tsk.

309
00:24:04,666 --> 00:24:07,353
You really have no heart.

310
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:08,820
Wait a second.

311
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:10,520
I don't see Dan or Choi.

312
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,833
I think they're both
seeing someone.

313
00:24:17,933 --> 00:24:18,933
Honey.

314
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:21,200
How do I look today?

315
00:24:23,266 --> 00:24:25,300
- Oh, jeez.
- What's wrong with her?

316
00:24:26,266 --> 00:24:28,753
I bought this online because

317
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,486
you said you like
girls in dresses.

318
00:24:30,566 --> 00:24:32,533
Well, it's not bad.

319
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:34,633
Oh, Honey.

320
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:37,620
Have one of these.

321
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:41,300
With some peanut sauce,
that's as sweet as you.

322
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:42,866
Say ah!

323
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:47,053
Ms. Dan…

324
00:24:47,133 --> 00:24:48,186
It's alright.

325
00:24:48,266 --> 00:24:49,286
And uh,

326
00:24:49,366 --> 00:24:51,686
I've been trying to tell you this,

327
00:24:51,766 --> 00:24:53,653
but even when we're in
a contract relationship,

328
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:57,753
I think calling each other
"Honey" is a bit too much.

329
00:24:57,833 --> 00:25:00,886
Besides, there wasn't a clause
like that in the contract.

330
00:25:00,966 --> 00:25:03,333
Oh, alright.

331
00:25:23,066 --> 00:25:24,386
Ms. Dan.

332
00:25:24,466 --> 00:25:28,253
Or maybe you forgot about
its context already?

333
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,900
Then let me remind you again.

334
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:36,153
One. The term of the
relationship is set as one month.

335
00:25:36,233 --> 00:25:37,553
There's still five days to go.

336
00:25:37,633 --> 00:25:38,953
I haven't forgotten.

337
00:25:39,033 --> 00:25:43,520
Two, no flirting with a third party
during the contract

338
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:45,520
relationship period.

339
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:49,033
Sure. I've no one else right now
besides you, Mr. Choi.

340
00:25:50,633 --> 00:25:52,586
Three, during the contract period,
we are to go on at least

341
00:25:52,666 --> 00:25:54,820
two dining dates a week.

342
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:58,453
Yes, and that's why we're
having lunch together, isn't it?

343
00:25:58,533 --> 00:26:01,500
So what's the problem?

344
00:26:02,466 --> 00:26:04,353
There's a clause about
annulment of contract.

345
00:26:04,433 --> 00:26:06,753
"No touching."

346
00:26:06,833 --> 00:26:09,286
Does that mean
our contract is annulled?

347
00:26:09,366 --> 00:26:11,453
Because I accidentally touched you
while reaching for the sauce?

348
00:26:11,533 --> 00:26:14,520
Well, I guess
it wasn't intentional,

349
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:16,620
so I'll just end that
as a warning this time.

350
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,020
But be careful from now on.

351
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:20,166
Sure, I'll be careful.

352
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,600
One second.

353
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:28,900
Yes, this is Choi Yun-hyuk.

354
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,420
Gosh, that was close.

355
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,753
annulment of contract?

356
00:26:38,833 --> 00:26:40,166
That was just too close.

357
00:26:41,866 --> 00:26:44,053
Left hand, you be careful.

358
00:26:44,133 --> 00:26:45,433
Warning, warning.

359
00:26:48,233 --> 00:26:50,153
Does she like me that much?

360
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:52,066
While I do understand…

361
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:57,100
Still, her love is just too much.

362
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:00,933
Anyway, what do I do?

363
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:04,933
I get that she's nice and cute,

364
00:27:07,133 --> 00:27:09,200
but my heart doesn't move.

365
00:27:10,466 --> 00:27:11,733
It just doesn't.

366
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:22,833
Jung-rok!

367
00:27:28,066 --> 00:27:30,986
I thought it was weird that
you stopped driving to work.

368
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:32,353
Have you been taking the bus
all this time?

369
00:27:32,433 --> 00:27:33,666
Yes, well…

370
00:27:36,566 --> 00:27:39,420
Well, I guess this is fate.
How about a glass of soju?

371
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:41,100
No, let's just go home.

372
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:46,933
Hey, wait up!

373
00:27:56,166 --> 00:27:57,520
Gosh, you're tired.

374
00:27:57,600 --> 00:28:00,086
You're tired, aren't you?

375
00:28:00,166 --> 00:28:02,253
You didn't get
any sleep last night?

376
00:28:02,333 --> 00:28:04,653
I don't have time to sleep.

377
00:28:04,733 --> 00:28:06,220
There's so much to memorize!

378
00:28:06,300 --> 00:28:07,253
Exactly.

379
00:28:07,333 --> 00:28:09,353
And with all those legal jargons,

380
00:28:09,433 --> 00:28:11,700
it's going to be real tough
memorizing it all, huh?

381
00:28:13,966 --> 00:28:15,320
But uh…

382
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,786
Working at the law firm has
actually helped a lot.

383
00:28:17,866 --> 00:28:20,753
I've heard most of the terms, so…

384
00:28:20,833 --> 00:28:24,020
It's easy memorizing them,
and understanding it, too.

385
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:25,233
We're here.

386
00:28:25,766 --> 00:28:27,786
What, already?

387
00:28:27,866 --> 00:28:30,533
Too bad, it'll be dawn
when you're finished.

388
00:28:32,933 --> 00:28:34,420
It's alright.

389
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:36,253
Ouch, my back!

390
00:28:36,333 --> 00:28:38,466
I should get out and
stretch my back.

391
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:41,033
Huh? Hello!

392
00:28:41,233 --> 00:28:43,320
Thank goodness.

393
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:45,533
She's back to where she was
so quickly.

394
00:28:52,466 --> 00:28:54,100
(Supreme Court Database)

395
00:28:59,633 --> 00:29:02,966
(Oh Yoon-seo At Rehearsal for
Her New Drama)

396
00:29:06,100 --> 00:29:08,400
(Oh Yoon-seo At Rehearsal for
Her New Drama)

397
00:29:09,033 --> 00:29:11,666
I guess she's doing fine now.

398
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,000
Cheers!

399
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,120
What's with that big bag?

400
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:32,266
This is a present for you.

401
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:36,033
These are masks to protect
your health from fine dust.

402
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:39,353
You mean not my health,

403
00:29:39,433 --> 00:29:42,320
but me, from other women, huh?

404
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:43,400
Yep!

405
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,586
Oh, and…

406
00:29:45,666 --> 00:29:49,233
These are cosmetics to make
your silky skin even smoother!

407
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,353
And these are vitamins to

408
00:29:51,433 --> 00:29:53,253
level up your charms!

409
00:29:53,333 --> 00:29:54,753
And these are…

410
00:29:54,833 --> 00:29:55,966
Hold on!

411
00:29:58,533 --> 00:30:00,286
Ms. Dan.

412
00:30:00,366 --> 00:30:02,053
Do you like me that much?

413
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:04,520
I mean, I know very well that

414
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:07,353
I'm an homme fatale, but…

415
00:30:07,433 --> 00:30:09,133
I'm starting to wonder if
you like me that much.

416
00:30:10,766 --> 00:30:11,686
Yes.

417
00:30:11,766 --> 00:30:14,853
You're so charming,
and the more I get to know you,

418
00:30:14,933 --> 00:30:16,300
the more I'm smitten.

419
00:30:19,333 --> 00:30:21,820
That's why it makes me sad.

420
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:23,453
I like you so much,

421
00:30:23,533 --> 00:30:27,400
but this happiness will
expire in 5 days, right?

422
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:36,686
Tell me honestly.

423
00:30:36,766 --> 00:30:42,620
How has it been for you
this past month?

424
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:44,686
After the five days,

425
00:30:44,766 --> 00:30:49,133
will you just end it with me,
without looking back?

426
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,900
Ms. Dan, you're a great person.

427
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:01,286
You take such good care of me,

428
00:31:01,366 --> 00:31:03,200
and there are
very cute sides to you.

429
00:31:05,066 --> 00:31:06,500
But how should I say this…

430
00:31:13,666 --> 00:31:16,953
My heart just doesn't move.

431
00:31:17,033 --> 00:31:18,100
What?

432
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:29,153
Are you alright, Ms. Dan?

433
00:31:29,233 --> 00:31:31,533
Why did you drink so much?

434
00:31:32,733 --> 00:31:34,053
Why, do you think?

435
00:31:34,133 --> 00:31:35,686
I like you so much,

436
00:31:35,766 --> 00:31:36,820
but when the contract term is up,

437
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:39,120
we'll just go back to being
what we used to be

438
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,933
and that's causing me grief.

439
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,400
But what can I do?

440
00:31:44,700 --> 00:31:48,333
It's all my fault for
not being able to move your heart.

441
00:32:38,366 --> 00:32:40,653
- Are you alright?
- Yes!

442
00:32:40,733 --> 00:32:42,000
I'm fine.

443
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:47,820
I'm relieved to hear that.

444
00:32:47,900 --> 00:32:49,366
I'm sorry.

445
00:32:56,166 --> 00:32:57,233
Uh…

446
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,120
What's that expression
on your face?

447
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,666
Don't tell me… You fell for him?

448
00:33:02,333 --> 00:33:06,520
Yes. Isn't he just great?

449
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,820
But just now, you said
something about how you like me,

450
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:10,653
and that's causing you grief.

451
00:33:10,733 --> 00:33:15,253
But you said you were
unmoved by me.

452
00:33:15,333 --> 00:33:17,500
See, I'm very quick
when it comes to giving up.

453
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,653
Um, excuse me!

454
00:33:22,733 --> 00:33:24,353
Ouch, my legs…

455
00:33:24,433 --> 00:33:26,786
I think I hurt my legs.

456
00:33:26,866 --> 00:33:27,986
So can I have your…

457
00:33:28,066 --> 00:33:30,433
I mean, can I have a ride?

458
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,300
Ohhh, my heart…

459
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:38,520
Why does my heart hurt?

460
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,153
See, I'm very quick
when it comes to giving up.

461
00:33:40,233 --> 00:33:41,300
Huh?

462
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,033
Yes, Mother.

463
00:33:46,666 --> 00:33:47,733
What, a marriage interview?

464
00:33:48,533 --> 00:33:50,820
Mother, I told you that
I'm not interested.

465
00:33:50,900 --> 00:33:52,833
Alright, I'm hanging up.

466
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:56,853
Mr. Lee, I see your mother is
trying to find someone for you.

467
00:33:56,933 --> 00:33:58,620
Yes.

468
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:01,586
But I have no intention of
going to a marriage interview.

469
00:34:01,666 --> 00:34:04,086
Because I'm one of those people

470
00:34:04,166 --> 00:34:07,453
you and your other half are
connected by destiny.

471
00:34:07,533 --> 00:34:09,286
Oh what?

472
00:34:09,366 --> 00:34:10,486
About your client's guardian.

473
00:34:10,566 --> 00:34:13,120
There's a limit to
how many times you can postpone.

474
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:15,320
I mean, this is just no manners.

475
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,653
Well, I'll reject their request

476
00:34:17,733 --> 00:34:20,686
and write to the Court separately
about the current process.

477
00:34:20,766 --> 00:34:21,986
Where's Kwon Jung-rok?

478
00:34:22,066 --> 00:34:23,120
- Ma'am…
- I said, where is he?

479
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:24,653
Ma'am, please calm down.

480
00:34:24,733 --> 00:34:27,920
Where's Kwon Jung-rok?
Where is he?

481
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,233
Kwon Jung-rok!

482
00:34:30,266 --> 00:34:32,086
There you are.

483
00:34:32,166 --> 00:34:35,286
You remember my son, don't you?

484
00:34:35,366 --> 00:34:39,253
My son, whom you turned into
a murderer in split second!

485
00:34:39,333 --> 00:34:40,800
Park Su-myung.

486
00:34:42,833 --> 00:34:44,753
Who was it that killed
Mr. Kim Hyung-tae that night?

487
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:48,353
The person who stabbed him was...

488
00:34:48,433 --> 00:34:49,720
The person who stabbed him was...!

489
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:51,553
Su-myung, no! Don't say anything!

490
00:34:51,633 --> 00:34:52,953
Ms. Lim, please calm down.

491
00:34:53,033 --> 00:34:54,920
Don't hit Yun-hee! Don't!

492
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,486
Don't hit her!

493
00:34:56,566 --> 00:35:01,186
I was so angry that
I came to see you.

494
00:35:01,266 --> 00:35:02,753
Ma'am, please calm down.

495
00:35:02,833 --> 00:35:03,786
Let go of me!

496
00:35:03,866 --> 00:35:05,286
Do you think I can calm down?

497
00:35:05,366 --> 00:35:08,200
When he turned my son
into a murderer?

498
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,033
My son, he…

499
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:14,820
He's not capable of
doing such a cruel thing,

500
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:17,833
stabbing a person to death!

501
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:25,520
Ma'am,

502
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:28,253
I understand how you feel,

503
00:35:28,333 --> 00:35:32,220
but this wasn't Mr. Kwon's
sole judgment.

504
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:34,620
The Court has given
their verdict already.

505
00:35:34,700 --> 00:35:35,766
Exactly!

506
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:38,286
Tomorrow's the last trial,

507
00:35:38,366 --> 00:35:40,386
so what will happen to my son?

508
00:35:40,466 --> 00:35:44,120
What if he's never allowed
outside again?

509
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:47,133
I won't ever forgive you,
if that happens!

510
00:35:47,966 --> 00:35:49,700
Ever!

511
00:35:52,733 --> 00:35:53,933
Ma'am…

512
00:35:58,100 --> 00:36:00,166
Kwon, don't take it to heart.

513
00:36:00,733 --> 00:36:02,720
All parents are the same.

514
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:06,686
When they're driven to
a corner like this,

515
00:36:06,766 --> 00:36:08,886
they desperately want to believe
their child's not guilty,

516
00:36:08,966 --> 00:36:10,966
and they lose their
sense of judgment.

517
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,986
Am I not right, Ms. Yang?

518
00:36:14,066 --> 00:36:16,520
Well, I have to agree.

519
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:20,220
Remember how my daughter was
framed last time?

520
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:22,486
Speaking from that experience,

521
00:36:22,566 --> 00:36:24,686
when you find that
your child's in a tough situation

522
00:36:24,766 --> 00:36:27,986
as a parent, you just can't
think rationally.

523
00:36:28,066 --> 00:36:30,420
Your mind goes blank,
and you can't think of anything.

524
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:34,120
I'm sure she needed someone
to vent her anger out on.

525
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:36,120
