Always, the law firm that's
leading this industry?

781
00:51:50,533 --> 00:51:52,186
I mean, he might not know me.

782
00:51:52,266 --> 00:51:53,820
So imagine how
shocked he might be.

783
00:51:53,900 --> 00:51:55,353
No, that's not what I…

784
00:51:55,433 --> 00:51:57,966
Whatever, just stop it already.

785
00:51:58,733 --> 00:52:02,320
I didn't know your tongue
was so loose, Ms. Yang.

786
00:52:02,400 --> 00:52:04,986
At this rate, you're going to
blab on about

787
00:52:05,066 --> 00:52:06,853
how I'm a highly respected lawyer,

788
00:52:06,933 --> 00:52:10,800
who's featured on many TV shows!

789
00:52:12,066 --> 00:52:16,220
Or why don't you just say that

790
00:52:16,300 --> 00:52:18,633
the law firm Yoon-seo worked at,
is ours?

791
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:22,966
Mr. Yeon!

792
00:52:27,433 --> 00:52:28,566
Yoon-seo…

793
00:52:29,533 --> 00:52:32,186
Yoon-seo is running toward me,

794
00:52:32,266 --> 00:52:33,966
while calling out my name.

795
00:52:37,166 --> 00:52:39,500
Ms. Yang! Hae-young!

796
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:41,853
How did you come here?

797
00:52:41,933 --> 00:52:44,486
I missed you guys so much.

798
00:52:44,566 --> 00:52:45,653
It's so good to see you!

799
00:52:45,733 --> 00:52:46,800
Me too.

800
00:52:47,766 --> 00:52:49,686
So what brings you here?

801
00:52:49,766 --> 00:52:50,900
All three of you?

802
00:52:51,300 --> 00:52:54,200
I sometimes take a walk
in front of the court, like this.

803
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:55,953
While reminding myself of
the resolve I made,

804
00:52:56,033 --> 00:52:59,586
to fight on the side of the weak.

805
00:52:59,666 --> 00:53:01,886
Today is one of those days.

806
00:53:01,966 --> 00:53:03,586
Today is one of those days?

807
00:53:03,666 --> 00:53:05,620
Yes, it's one of those days.

808
00:53:05,700 --> 00:53:06,786
Anyway, this is great.

809
00:53:06,866 --> 00:53:09,553
My shooting's been delayed
so I have some free time.

810
00:53:09,633 --> 00:53:10,953
You're yet to have lunch, right?

811
00:53:11,033 --> 00:53:12,866
How about we all go for lunch?

812
00:53:19,433 --> 00:53:21,253
Why are you looking
at me like that?

813
00:53:21,333 --> 00:53:22,420
Go on, eat.

814
00:53:22,500 --> 00:53:23,820
I just can't believe this is real.

815
00:53:23,900 --> 00:53:26,386
It feels like dining with
a celebrity right now.

816
00:53:26,466 --> 00:53:28,220
- What?
- Same here.

817
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:30,420
When I saw you on the set,

818
00:53:30,500 --> 00:53:32,586
it finally sunk that
you are an actress, Yoon-seo.

819
00:53:32,666 --> 00:53:34,620
I still can't believe that

820
00:53:34,700 --> 00:53:36,620
we'd chat so casually back then.

821
00:53:36,700 --> 00:53:39,386
Don't be like that,
it's so awkward.

822
00:53:39,466 --> 00:53:41,286
And I feel like there's
a distance between us now.

823
00:53:41,366 --> 00:53:43,886
Besides, you've no idea
how much I missed you guys.

824
00:53:43,966 --> 00:53:45,033
Really?

825
00:53:46,566 --> 00:53:47,853
You even missed us?

826
00:53:47,933 --> 00:53:48,933
Yes.

827
00:53:49,500 --> 00:53:53,120
I knew you'd feel my absence,

828
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:55,766
but this is quite embarrassing,
hearing it directly from you.

829
00:53:56,700 --> 00:53:58,520
You haven't changed
at all, Mr. Yeon.

830
00:53:58,600 --> 00:53:59,600
No.

831
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:03,220
Is everyone else doing well?

832
00:54:03,300 --> 00:54:06,520
Well, Mr. Choi and Ms. Dan
seem to be really busy.

833
00:54:06,600 --> 00:54:09,820
I think they're both
seeing someone.

834
00:54:09,900 --> 00:54:13,333
And Mr. Lee of course, is
as sentimental as always.

835
00:54:16,166 --> 00:54:19,020
Mr. Kwon is doing well too, is he?

836
00:54:19,100 --> 00:54:20,753
Well? Ha!

837
00:54:20,833 --> 00:54:23,353
I'm worried that

838
00:54:23,433 --> 00:54:25,033
he'll cause trouble soon.

839
00:54:26,466 --> 00:54:30,833
I think he's going to say
he'll defend Park Su-myung.

840
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:32,233
What?

841
00:54:33,100 --> 00:54:34,766
Park Su-myung…?

842
00:54:48,600 --> 00:54:53,386
Mr. Kwon, how are you doing?

843
00:54:53,466 --> 00:54:57,266
I was just thinking about you,
and…

844
00:55:09,966 --> 00:55:12,366
(Corrections)

845
00:55:15,833 --> 00:55:18,566
Do you remember me?

846
00:55:21,066 --> 00:55:22,620
Yes, I remember you.

847
00:55:22,700 --> 00:55:26,653
Your mother came to see me.

848
00:55:26,733 --> 00:55:28,800
And asked me to help you.

849
00:55:29,733 --> 00:55:36,153
So please answer me honestly.

850
00:55:36,233 --> 00:55:38,486
Alright, I will.

851
00:55:38,566 --> 00:55:43,653
I was told you only stabbed
Ms. Lim's husband just once.

852
00:55:43,733 --> 00:55:44,966
Is this true?

853
00:55:45,933 --> 00:55:47,653
That's right,

854
00:55:47,733 --> 00:55:49,753
I stabbed him once.

855
00:55:49,833 --> 00:55:51,953
That man beat her every day,

856
00:55:52,033 --> 00:55:55,066
so I got so mad and stabbed him.

857
00:55:56,266 --> 00:55:58,020
And Yun-hee told me to run.

858
00:55:58,100 --> 00:55:59,520
So I listened to her.

859
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:01,566
I ran away.

860
00:56:04,700 --> 00:56:06,500
By the way, where's Mom?

861
00:56:08,033 --> 00:56:09,620
Mom's having a hard time.

862
00:56:09,700 --> 00:56:11,700
I need to help her.

863
00:56:12,200 --> 00:56:13,853
I need to help Mom.

864
00:56:13,933 --> 00:56:15,620
I need to make deliveries…

865
00:56:15,700 --> 00:56:16,686
Mom…

866
00:56:16,766 --> 00:56:20,200
I don't want Mom to
have a hard time anymore.

867
00:56:21,033 --> 00:56:23,586
I honestly only stabbed him once.

868
00:56:23,666 --> 00:56:25,566
Just once.

869
00:56:56,533 --> 00:56:58,133
Kwon, are you crazy?

870
00:56:59,233 --> 00:57:02,766
Must you defend Park Su-myung?

871
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:06,600
Yes.

872
00:57:09,466 --> 00:57:11,886
Alright, let's say,

873
00:57:11,966 --> 00:57:15,953
you're right and the
real murderer is out there.

874
00:57:16,033 --> 00:57:19,033
But you'll get hurt, for
accusing the wrong person!

875
00:57:19,400 --> 00:57:23,186
But let's say Park Su-myung is
his murderer after all.

876
00:57:23,266 --> 00:57:24,520
Either way, you'll be hounded at.

877
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:27,720
For accusing someone when
you're not even sure.

878
00:57:27,800 --> 00:57:31,220
They'll think you're blatant to
defend him after all this time.

879
00:57:31,300 --> 00:57:34,820
And accuse you of
being inconsistent.

880
00:57:34,900 --> 00:57:39,320
This will test the
public trust on lawyers.

881
00:57:39,400 --> 00:57:41,366
I already gave him word
that I'll defend him.

882
00:57:42,500 --> 00:57:44,920
I even notified the Court already.

883
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:46,033
What?

884
00:57:48,700 --> 00:57:49,686
I'm sorry.

885
00:57:49,766 --> 00:57:50,833
Oh, you're sorry?

886
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:55,553
If you're so sorry,
then why did you do it?

887
00:57:55,633 --> 00:57:59,186
This is serious matter, so
why did you decide on your own?

888
00:57:59,266 --> 00:58:02,286
I knew you'd oppose me to the end,

889
00:58:02,366 --> 00:58:03,320
so I had no choice.

890
00:58:03,400 --> 00:58:06,300
You don't take my warnings
seriously, do you?

891
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:08,900
- Mr. Yeon.
- Ha!

892
00:58:10,100 --> 00:58:12,420
Do you even see me as your boss?

893
00:58:12,500 --> 00:58:14,153
Kwon.

894
00:58:14,233 --> 00:58:16,153
I mean, Jung-rok.

895
00:58:16,233 --> 00:58:18,453
Now the whole world will
point their finger at you.

896
00:58:18,533 --> 00:58:20,320
Do you think there will be
anyone out there who's on your side?

897
00:58:20,400 --> 00:58:23,020
After accusing an innocent man
and turning him into a murderer,

898
00:58:23,100 --> 00:58:25,986
now you're going back on your word
and admitting it was your mistake.

899
00:58:26,066 --> 00:58:27,220
But I have to.

900
00:58:27,300 --> 00:58:28,733
It was my mistake, after all.

901
00:58:31,400 --> 00:58:34,286
Though it's late,
I'd like to set things right.

902
00:58:34,366 --> 00:58:37,733
Right, you and
your sense of justice.

903
00:58:38,100 --> 00:58:40,220
But there isn't anyone out there
who'll think that

904
00:58:40,300 --> 00:58:41,453
you're doing this for justice.

905
00:58:41,533 --> 00:58:44,353
The world will brand you
as a lawyer

906
00:58:44,433 --> 00:58:46,100
who takes the Court for a show!

907
00:58:48,766 --> 00:58:51,220
As I told you, that is
solely my burden…

908
00:58:51,300 --> 00:58:52,286
Then what about us?

909
00:58:52,366 --> 00:58:54,286
What about everyone at Always?

910
00:58:54,366 --> 00:58:56,853
Don't you care about the
criticisms they'll face?

911
00:58:56,933 --> 00:58:58,353
If you ever considered us family,

912
00:58:58,433 --> 00:59:01,686
or cared about us,

913
00:59:01,766 --> 00:59:03,266
you can't do this to me.

914
00:59:04,700 --> 00:59:06,466
You can't do this to me,
do you understand me?

915
00:59:27,966 --> 00:59:31,953
I heard you were given the power
of attorney for that Park case.

916
00:59:32,033 --> 00:59:33,653
What happened?

917
00:59:33,733 --> 00:59:34,686
Well, that’s how it is.

918
00:59:34,766 --> 00:59:36,520
Tsk, you…

919
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:39,186
The risks may be
bigger than you think,

920
00:59:39,266 --> 00:59:41,133
so must you do this?

921
01:00:01,066 --> 01:00:02,866
I'm scared too.

922
01:00:05,233 --> 01:00:08,086
I still don’t know
what the truth is,

923
01:00:08,166 --> 01:00:10,853
but I'm scared that
my rash judgments

924
01:00:10,933 --> 01:00:13,666
may have driven someone to
a corner.

925
01:00:16,833 --> 01:00:17,866
I'm scared that

926
01:00:20,766 --> 01:00:23,886
I may leave a scar

927
01:00:23,966 --> 01:00:25,933
that will never heal,

928
01:00:33,300 --> 01:00:34,600
in someone's heart.

929
01:00:35,833 --> 01:00:37,753
But…

930
01:00:37,833 --> 01:00:39,833
If I were to ignore this

931
01:00:42,300 --> 01:00:44,933
and miss this chance to
correct my mistakes,

932
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:53,033
I may not have the confidence to

933
01:00:55,233 --> 01:00:58,233
represent anyone again.

934
01:01:33,700 --> 01:01:35,300
(Kim Hae-young)

935
01:01:38,233 --> 01:01:39,586
Great picture, right?

936
01:01:39,666 --> 01:01:42,366
Come drop by sometime, Yoon-seo.

937
01:01:47,933 --> 01:01:52,786
By the way, Mr. Kwon will be
taking that case after all.

938
01:01:52,866 --> 01:01:54,520
So things have really been
scary between Mr. Kwon

939
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:57,286
and Mr. Yeon after they had a row.

940
01:01:57,366 --> 01:01:59,453
I can only imagine the
burden on Mr. Kwon's shoulders,

941
01:01:59,533 --> 01:02:02,400
when he now has
no secretary to support him.

942
01:02:11,800 --> 01:02:14,133
(Prosecution Service)

943
01:02:12,966 --> 01:02:14,220
What?

944
01:02:14,300 --> 01:02:16,286
Kwon Jung-rok will be
defending Park Su-myung?

945
01:02:16,366 --> 01:02:18,266
Yes, that's what I heard.

946
01:02:19,266 --> 01:02:22,986
Ha! When was the time

947
01:02:23,066 --> 01:02:25,253
he accused him of
being the murderer?

948
01:02:25,333 --> 01:02:27,466
And now he wants to defend him?

949
01:02:32,000 --> 01:02:33,866
Funny guy, isn't he?

950
01:02:41,600 --> 01:02:44,300
Sir, I'm Koo Sung-gil from
Daehan Daily.

951
01:02:44,966 --> 01:02:48,253
I hear Mr. Park Su-myung
will be appealing.

952
01:02:48,333 --> 01:02:49,366
Is this true?

953
01:02:50,833 --> 01:02:52,153
Well…

954
01:02:52,233 --> 01:02:54,700
Even if he does,
things won't change much.

955
01:02:57,166 --> 01:02:58,166
By the way,

956
01:02:59,900 --> 01:03:02,400
there's an interesting
rumor that I heard.

957
01:03:05,800 --> 01:03:07,033
Mr. Kwon Jung-rok.

958
01:03:07,933 --> 01:03:09,686
Why did you go back on your word

959
01:03:09,766 --> 01:03:11,153
after accusing
Mr. Park of being the offender?

960
01:03:11,233 --> 01:03:13,786
That means an innocent man is
being locked up in prison right now.

961
01:03:13,866 --> 01:03:15,086
Don't you feel guilty about it?

962
01:03:15,166 --> 01:03:16,953
Some are even saying this is
against the lawyers' code of ethics.

963
01:03:17,033 --> 01:03:18,320
What do you have to say to that?

964
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:20,586
Is it true that you'll be
defending him for money?

965
01:03:20,666 --> 01:03:22,886
A lawyer who will be defending
a man forced a confession out of

966
01:03:22,966 --> 01:03:26,286
for his previous client…

967
01:03:26,366 --> 01:03:28,386
And once again,
they'll be pleading not guilty.

968
01:03:28,466 --> 01:03:29,786
What are your thoughts?

969
01:03:29,866 --> 01:03:32,253
Article 22 of the
Lawyer Code of Ethics

970
01:03:32,333 --> 01:03:33,453
states that where there is
a conflict of interest

971
01:03:33,533 --> 01:03:36,120
between two or more parties
involved in the same affair,

972
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:37,986
lawyers should refrain from
representing multiple parties.

973
01:03:38,066 --> 01:03:40,120
In other case,
this is just not on.

974
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:42,720
There's hardly a case like this
in the industry.

975
01:03:42,800 --> 01:03:44,253
I think the Bar Association…

976
01:03:44,333 --> 01:03:46,386
What do we do?

977
01:03:46,466 --> 01:03:49,400
Right, his decision hasn't been
met favorably.

978
01:03:53,133 --> 01:03:55,966
Let's stop watching,
it'll only trouble you.

979
01:03:58,366 --> 01:04:00,720
When I was troubled,

980
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:03,900
Mr. Kwon would always
be there for me.

981
01:04:22,900 --> 01:04:24,766
Um, Mr. Kwon?

982
01:04:28,500 --> 01:04:32,353
Don't mind what others are saying.

983
01:04:32,433 --> 01:04:35,966
Because I believe
you're going to win.

984
01:05:10,733 --> 01:05:12,500
(Say a wish)

985
01:05:16,566 --> 01:05:19,053
(Park Su-myung case file)

986
01:05:19,133 --> 01:05:22,000
(Supreme Court's Verdict on
Abetting Murder)

987
01:05:25,966 --> 01:05:29,486
Mr. Kwon, how have you been?

988
01:05:29,566 --> 01:05:33,020
I think I know
what I want for my wish now.

989
01:05:33,100 --> 01:05:37,820
My wish is to
never see you waiver.

990
01:05:37,900 --> 01:05:39,686
And just like you always have,

991
01:05:39,766 --> 01:05:43,100
I'm sure you'll pull through this.

992
01:07:51,433 --> 01:07:53,300
(Thank you to Song Kang for
his special cameo appearance)

993
01:08:23,900 --> 01:08:25,600
(Touch Your Heart)

994
01:08:25,600 --> 01:08:27,820
I may have ruined someone's life,

995
01:08:27,900 --> 01:08:29,753
so I need to make
things right again.

996
01:08:29,833 --> 01:08:31,453
- Here's my resignation letter.
- Do what you want.

997
01:08:31,533 --> 01:08:32,886
Because I don't need someone

998
01:08:32,966 --> 01:08:34,053
who's irresponsible like you.

999
01:08:34,133 --> 01:08:34,986
Do what you want.

1000
01:08:35,066 --> 01:08:36,053
You're not in
middle school anymore.

1001
01:08:36,133 --> 01:08:38,100
Why are you two fighting?

1002
01:08:38,866 --> 01:08:40,720
Going to work now, Mr. Kwon?

1003
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:43,053
I'm going to come see you
when I want to.

1004
01:08:43,133 --> 01:08:45,520
Mr. Kwon, do you want to
have dinner with me?

1005
01:08:45,600 --> 01:08:47,286
Why are you doing this?

1006
01:08:47,366 --> 01:08:48,720
It's all just to save a life.

1007
01:08:48,800 --> 01:08:52,786
Who else? Kwon, who's become
the national enemy.

1008
01:08:52,866 --> 01:08:56,420
My wish is to
never see you waiver.

1009
01:08:56,500 --> 01:08:59,633
And just like you always have,
I'm sure you'll pull through this.
